{
  "stem": "8423.4",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then we had to pick up these rocks and carry-- carry them to a certain place where they were building a road out of rocks.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And if you didn't pick up a-- a rock large enough to suit them, or you weren't moving fast enough, the guards beat you.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And now, some of these guards were political prisoners.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They weren't Germans.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But you know, they seemed to be just as mean.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Like for instance, the woman who was in charge of us, that [INAUDIBLE], when we complained about anything, she said, oh, you think you have it tough?",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She said, you should have seen it when we came here years ago.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We didn't even have a roof over our head.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We built these barracks.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So you are lucky you have a roof over your head.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And also, during separation-- oh, we didn't consider them being part of us, even though they were prisoners, because they were in charge of us and treated us, you know, like if we were just dirt, because they were our bosses.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they got better food, better quarters.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They lived in the barrack, but they had like a whole little partition just to themselves.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they had a little stove.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We could smell them cooking in there, when we were so starving, you know?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Anyhow, this woman was so cruel, that when we first were separated from our parents, we had asked, you know, when we would be reunited.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they were saying, even as we were being separated, don't fret because it's very temporary.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "On Sunday, you will all be reunited with your families.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You're just being separated for work.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
